com.salesforce.androidsdk.ui
Class SalesforceR

java.lang.Object
  com.salesforce.androidsdk.ui.SalesforceR

public class SalesforceR
extends java.lang.Object

Before 1.3, SalesforceSDK was packaged as a jar which can't have resources. All the methods were returning -1 and a project using the SDK had to provide a subclass returning actual resource ids. Since 1.3, SalesforceSDK is packaged as a library project and therefore contains its resources. We are only keeping this class for backward compatibility reason, for projects that use the SDK as a jar or that have provided custom screens (login, passcode etc) and used SalesforceR to point to their own screens.
